                <pb n="1"/>
                <p>1537 North Eighth St.<lb/>
                Oct. 6th. 89<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Doctor<lb/></p>
            <p>My mother<lb/> and sisters join me<lb/> in trusting that you fasted<lb/> well&#44; and have somewhat<lb/> recovered from the fatigue<lb/> consequent upon your<lb/> extra exertion.  I don&#39;t know<lb/> how you managed to<lb/> blow the Shophar so beautifully<lb/> after all you went through<lb/> fasting and reading.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am very sorry<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I vexed you about the ink&#45;stand<lb/> but the motive that prompted<lb/> me was a purely selfish one.<lb/>  I wanted you to have some&#45;<lb/>thing in your study&#44; which<lb/> might induce you to bestow<lb/> an occasional thought&#44; upon<lb/> what to me were the<lb/> pleasant and instructive<lb/> hours I spent with you.<lb/>  Trusting that the coming<lb/> Holydays will be pleasant<lb/> ones for your&#45;self and family<lb/> I am with regards<lb/></p>
            <p><sic>Your&#39;s</sic> truly<lb/> Charity S. Cohen.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. S. Morais.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Revd. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5th.<lb/>
                City<lb/></p>
            </body>
